aa(lp168
VYou see, the Indians also had a river
p169
aVthat separates the land of the living from the land of the dead.
p170
aVBut you don't cross it once.
p171
aVYou go to and fro endlessly.
p172
aVIt was called the Vaitarani.
p173
aVYou go again and again and again.
p174
aVBecause, you see,
p175
aVnothing lasts forever in India, not even death.
p176
aVAnd so, you have these grand rituals
p177
aVwhere great images of mother goddesses are built
p178
aVand worshiped for 10 days ...
p179
aVAnd what do you do at the end of 10 days?
p180
aVYou dunk it in the river.
p181
aVBecause it has to end.
p182
aVAnd next year, she will come back.
p183
aVWhat goes around always comes around,
p184
aVand this rule applies not just to man,
p185
aVbut also the gods.
p186
aVYou see, the gods
p187
aVhave to come back again and again and again
p188
aVas Ram, as Krishna.
p189
aVNot only do they live infinite lives,
p190
aVbut the same life is lived infinite times
p191
aVtill you get to the point of it all.
p192
aV"Groundhog Day."
p193
aV(Laughter)
